Overleden","1421–Female":"1421–Overleden","1501":"1501","1500":"1500","1421":"1421","1442":"1442","1475":"1475","1441":"1441","1450":"1450","1470":"1470",", Shropshire, , England":"Shropshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk",", , , England":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1442–1470":"1442–1470","1450–1501":"1450–1501","1475–1500":"1475–1500","1421–Male":"1421–Deceased","1421–Female":"1421–Deceased","1501":"1501","1500":"1500","1421":"1421","1442":"1442","1475":"1475","1441":"1441","1450":"1450","1470":"1470",", Shropshire, , England":"Shropshire, England, United Kingdom",", , , England":"England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Sperry","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Leicestershire): from the early Middle English personal name <i>Sperry</i> (Old Norse <i>Sperrir</i>, perhaps originally a nickname for a tall man, from Old Norse <i>sperra</i> ‘spar, beam, stake’)."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Joan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Contracted form of Old French <i>Jo(h)anne</i>, from Latin <i>Io(h)anna</i> (  see  Joanna  ). In England this was the usual feminine form of   John   from the Middle English period onwards and was extremely popular, but in the 16th and 17th centuries it steadily lost ground to   Jane .  It was strongly revived in the first part of the 20th century, partly under the influence of  George Bernard Shaw's  play St Joan (  1923 ), based on the life of  Joan of Arc  (  1412–31 ). Claiming to be guided by the voices of the saints, she persuaded the French dauphin to defy the occupying English forces and have himself crowned, and she led the French army that raised the siege of Orleans in  1429 . The following year she was captured by the Burgundians and sold to the English, and a year later she was burned at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Joan Sperry was born in 1442, in Shropshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Sperry, was 21 and her mother, Sperry, was 21. She had at least 1 son with William Wolcott I. She died in 1470, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 28."},"et":{"1442–1470":"1442–1470","1450–1501":"1450–1501","1475–1500":"1475–1500","1421–Male":"1421–Surnud","1421–Female":"1421–Surnud","1501":"1501","1500":"1500","1421":"1421","1442":"1442","1475":"1475","1441":"1441","1450":"1450","1470":"1470",", Shropshire, , England":"Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom",", , , England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1442–1470":"1442–1470","1450–1501":"1450–1501","1475–1500":"1475–1500","1421–Male":"1421–Kuollut","1421–Female":"1421–Kuollut","1501":"1501","1500":"1500","1421":"1421","1442":"1442","1475":"1475","1441":"1441","1450":"1450","1470":"1470",", Shropshire, , England":"Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta",", , , England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1442–1470":"1442–1470","1450–1501":"1450–1501","1475–1500":"1475–1500","1421–Male":"1421–Décédé","1421–Female":"1421–Décédée","1501":"1501","1500":"1500","1421":"1421","1442":"1442","1475":"1475","1441":"1441","1450":"1450","1470":"1470",", Shropshire, , England":"Shropshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni",", , , England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Joan Sperry est née en 1442, à Shropshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, son père, Sperry, avait 21 ans et sa mère, Sperry, avait 21 ans. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec William Wolcott I. Elle est décédée en 1470, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 28 ans."},"de":{"1442–1470":"1442–1470","1450–1501":"1450–1501","1475–1500":"1475–1500","1421–Male":"1421–Verstorben","1421–Female":"1421–Verstorben","1501":"1501","1500":"1500","1421":"1421","1442":"1442","1475":"1475","1441":"1441","1450":"1450","1470":"1470",", Shropshire, , England":"Shropshire, England, United Kingdom",", , , England":"England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Als Joan Sperry 1442 in Shropshire, England, United Kingdom geboren wurde, war ihr Vater Sperry 21 und ihre Mutter Sperry 21. Sie hatte mit William Wolcott I mindestens 1 Sohn. Sie starb 1470 im Alter von 28 Jahren in England, United Kingdom."},"ht":{"1442–1470":"1442–1470","1450–1501":"1450–1501","1475–1500":"1475–1500","1421–Male":"1421–Desede","1421–Female":"1421–Desede","1501":"1501","1500":"1500","1421":"1421","1442":"1442","1475":"1475","1441":"1441","1450":"1450","1470":"1470",", Shropshire, , England":"Shropshire, Angletè, United Kingdom",", , , England":"Angletè, United Kingdom"},"hu":{"1442–1470":"1442–1470","1450–1501":"1450–1501","1475–1500":"1475–1500","1421–Male":"1421–elhunyt","1421–Female":"1421–elhunyt","1501":"1501","1500":"1500","1421":"1421","1442":"1442","1475":"1475","1441":"1441","1450":"1450","1470":"1470",", Shropshire, , England":"Shropshire, Anglia, United Kingdom",", , , England":"Anglia, United Kingdom"},"id":{"1442–1470":"1442–1470","1450–1501":"1450–1501","1475–1500":"1475–1500","1421–Male":"1421–Telah Meninggal","1421–Female":"1421–Telah Meninggal","1501":"1501","1500":"1500","1421":"1421","1442":"1442","1475":"1475","1441":"1441","1450":"1450","1470":"1470",", Shropshire, , England":"Shropshire, Inggris, United Kingdom",", , , England":"Inggris, United Kingdom"},"it":{"1442–1470":"1442–1470","1450–1501":"1450–1501","1475–1